3. Of the uncertainty of Mans life; The time paſt is gone, as if it had never beene; the time to come is uncertaine, we are altogether unſure of it; wee have no time but 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 this very inſtant; and wee know not how long we ſhall hold that: It was the ſaying of one of our owne Poets,
Fleres, ſi ſcires unum tua tempora menſem;
Rides, cum non ſit forſitan una dies.
